parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or failure of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially in high-speed or heavy-traffic conditions.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
loss of power
reduced speed
difficulty shifting gears
warning lights or indicators appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of lifters can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and reduced speed, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in heavy-traffic conditions.
symptoms: The engine jolts
sputters
or stalls
reduced speed acceleration
warning lights or indicators appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine springs can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and reduced speed, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in heavy-traffic conditions.
symptoms: The engine knocks
stalls
or shuts off
warning lights or indicators appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause the engine to stall, leaving the driver stranded, and increasing the risk of accidents, especially in high-speed or heavy-traffic conditions.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off
warning lights or indicators appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure due to Water Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the vehicle's electrical system can cause electrical shorts, leading to potential fires, loss of critical safety features, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle
electrical shorts
warning messages or lights on the dashboard
loss of safety features such as airbags or rear safety packages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, particularly for rear seat passengers.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights or messages
failure of airbags to deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rear safety package, including blind spot monitoring, rear cross traffic alert, and rear parking sensors, can increase the risk of accidents, particularly when reversing or changing lanes.
symptoms: Warning lights or messages on the dashboard
loss of rear safety features
HVAC system malfunction (e.g.
fan stuck on high).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Power Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump power control module can cause the engine to stall suddenly, even at high speeds, which can lead to fatal accidents or serious safety hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power while driving
the engine stalls suddenly
the vehicle is unable to start
the check engine light comes on after multiple failed start attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden loss of power and transmission failure can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and may lead to costly repairs or even require replacement.
symptoms: The transmission unexpectedly downshifts into neutral
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle will not restart or shift out of park
the vehicle rolls to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Internal engine failure can cause catastrophic engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even require replacement, and may cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the vehicle will not start
internal engine bearing material is found in the oil
bearings are spun causing catastrophic engine failure
crankshaft main bearing cap is discolored from extreme heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: BCM failure can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into neutral and rolls to a stop
the engine shuts off
the vehicle will not restart or shift out of park.
